    <p>Join nine-year-old Na­dine and her grand­fa­ther as they chat about liv­ing and grow­ing up in Sin­ga­pore. They ex­plore topics such as Na­tional Day Pa­rades, places of recre­ation, cul­tural fes­ti­vals and cam­paigns. Each chap­ter fea­tures il­lus­tra­tions by lo­cal artists, archival pho­tos and videos, games and quizzes. This is the dig­i­tal com­pan­ion to Home, Truly: Grow­ing Up With Sin­ga­pore, 1950s To The Present, an ex­hi­bi­tion that will run from De­cem­ber this year to Au­gust next year at the Na­tional Mu­seum of Sin­ga­pore. It is pre­sented in col­lab­o­ra­tion with The Straits Times. WHEN: Till Dec 31 AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: str.sg/JBZq</p>


